  <thing id="cS2ExSlvrF" name="The Exorcist of the Silver Flame" description="The Church of the Silver Flame is dedicated to fighting supernatural forces of evil across Khorvaire. Trying to remain above the lingering confl icts of the Last War, the church focuses its energy on combating extraplanar threats such as possessing devils and corrupting demons. Leading this unceasing war are the exorcists of the Silver Flame, spiritual heroes who channel the power of the Silver Flame to ward off evil outsiders, cast out possessing spirits, and smite the material forms of the forces of evil.\n\nExorcists of the Silver Flame are drawn from the ranks of the most experienced and dedicated champions of the church, primarily clerics and paladins. Multiclass cleric/wizards (and accomplished mystic theurges of the church) are also drawn to the class, though most of these retain their emphasis on divine spells and powers.\n\nMost exorcists of the Silver Flame are active in the world, out on the front lines of the war against evil. A few NPC exorcists might be found in a state of retirement - so physically and emotionally scarred from their experiences that their minds border on insanity." compset="ClassLevel" maxlimit="10">
    <usesource source="S2Eberron"/>
    <tag group="ClassType" tag="Prestige"/>
    <tag group="ProductId" tag="HLCommunit"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="NoPathSoc"/>
    <bootstrap thing="cHelpESF"></bootstrap>
    <link linkage="helper" thing="cHelpESF"/>
    <exprreq message="Knowledge (religion) 5+ ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[skKnowRel] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Ability to cast 1st-level Divine spells required."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Divine] >= 1 + 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Good alignment required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Alignment.Good] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Worshiper of the Silver Flame required."><![CDATA[#hasdeity[deiSilvFla] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Knowledge (the planes) 1+ ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[skKnowPlan] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cEsfFlameC" name="Flame of Censure" description="The Exorcist of the Silver Flame&apos;s class level stacks with levels in any other class that grants the channel energy ability.\n\nAn exorcist of the Silver Flame can manifest the mystical power of the Silver Flame to ward off outsiders with the evil subtype.  Their channel energy ability can now effect evil outsiders as if they where undead. An evil outsider is stunned for 1 round by the power of the Silver Flame channeled through the exorcist if they fail their will save vs channel energy. If the exorcist&apos;s character level is at least twice the outsider&apos;s Hit Dice, she banishes the outsider back to its home plane on a failed save." compset="ClSpecial">
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="15000"><![CDATA[
~ If we're disabled, just get out now
doneif (tagis[Helper.SpcDisable] <> 0)
      
~ If we don't have any channelling, we're also done.
doneif (hero.tagis[Hero.Channel] = 0)
      
~ We passed, so give us a selector to choose among the xChannels
field[usrCandid1].text = "component.Ability & thingid.xChannel"
perform assign[ChooseSrc1.Hero]
      
~ Stop if we haven't chosen anything
doneif (field[usrChosen1].ischosen = 0) 
      
field[usrChosen1].chosen.field[abValue].value += field[xTotalLev].value]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cEsfWepExo" name="Weapon of the Exorcist" description="An exorcist of the Silver Flame chooses a weapon with which she dispenses the will of the church. The chosen weapon must be a weapon that the exorcist of the Silver Flame is proficient with, and must have been in her possession for the last 24 hours. While wielding this weapon, the exorcist has a +1 sacred bonus on damage rolls, and she treats it as a magic weapon for the purpose of overcoming damage reduction.\n\nAn exorcist of the Silver Flame may only have one weapon of the exorcist at a time." compset="ClSpecial">
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="fShowWhat" tag="Weapons"/>
    <tag group="ChooseSrc1" tag="Hero"/>
