  <thing id="cArtItemCr" name="Item Creation" description="An artificer can create a magic item even if he does not have access to the spells that are prerequisites for the item. The artificer must make a successful Use Magic Device check (DC 20 + caster level) to emulate each spell normally required to create the item. Thus, to make a 1st-level {i}wand of magic missile,{/i} an artificer would need a Use Magic Device check result of 21 or higher. To create a {i}bottle of air{/i} (caster level 7th), he would need a check result of 27 or higher to emulate the {i}water breathing{/i} prerequisite.\n\nThe artificer must make a successful check for each prerequisite for each item he makes. If he fails a check, he can try again each day until the item is complete. If he comes to the end of the crafting time and he has still not successfully emulated one of the powers, he can make one final check - his last-ditch effort, even if he has already made a check that day. If that check also fails, then the creation process fails and the time, money, and XP expended to craft the item are lost.\n\nFor purposes of meeting item prerequisites, an artificer&apos;s effective caster level equals his artificer level +2. If the item duplicates a spell effect, however, it uses the artificer&apos;s actual level as its caster level. Costs are always determined using the item&apos;s minimum caster level or the artificer&apos;s actual level (if it is higher). Thus, a 3rd-level artificer can make a scroll of {i}fi reball,{/i} since the minimum caster level for {i}fi reball{/i} is 5th. He pays the normal cost for making such a scroll with a caster level of 5th: 5x3x12.5 = 187 gp and 5 sp, plus 15 XP. But the scroll&apos;s actual caster level is only 3rd, and it produces a weak {i}fi reball{/i} that deals only 3d6 points of damage.\n\nAn artificer can also make Use Magic Device checks to emulate nonspell requirements, including alignment and race, using the normal DCs for the skill. He cannot emulate skill or feat requirements, however, including item creation feat prerequisites. He must meet the caster level prerequisite, including the minimum level to cast a spell he stores in a potion, wand, or scroll. An artificer&apos;s infusions do not meet spell prerequisites for creating magic items. For example, an artificer must still employ the Use Magic Device skill to emulate the {i}light{/i} spell to create a {i}wand of light,{/i} even though {i}light{/i} appears on his infusion list." compset="ClSpecial"></thing>
  <thing id="cArtCraftR" name="Craft Reserve" description="An artificer receives a pool of points he can spend instead of gold when crafting a magic item. Each time the artificer gains a new level, he receives a new craft reserve; leftover points from the previous level do not carry over. If the points are not spent, they are lost. An artificer can also use his craft reserve to supplement the gp cost of the item he is making, taking a portion of the cost from his craft reserve and a portion from his own gp.\n\n{B}Pathfinder:{/b} Changed XP to gp instead at ten times the value." compset="ClSpecial">
