  <thing id="cArtCraftH" name="Craft Homunculus" description="At 4th level, an artificer can create a homunculus as if he had the Craft Construct feat. He must emulate the spell requirements ({i}arcane eye, mending,{/i} and {i}mirror image{/i}) as normal for making a magic item, and he must pay all the usual gold and XP costs (though he can spend points from his craft reserve). An artificer can also upgrade an existing homunculus that he owns, adding 1 Hit Die at a cost of 2,000 gp and 160 XP.{br}{br}If an artificer gives his homunculus more than 6 Hit Dice, it becomes a Small creature and advances as described in the {i}Monster Manual{/i} (+4 Str, -2 Dex, damage increases to 1d6). The homunculus also gains 10 extra hit points for being a Small construct.{br}{br}An artificer&apos;s homunculus can have as many Hit Dice as its master&apos;s Hit Dice minus 2. No matter how many Hit Dice it has, a homunculus never grows larger than Small." compset="ClSpecial" summary="An artificer can create a homunculus as if he had the Craft Construct feat.">
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cArtRetEss" name="Retain Essence" description="At 5th level, an artificer gains the ability to salvage the gp from a magic item and use those points to create another magic item. The artificer must spend a day with the item, and he must also have the appropriate item creation feat for the item he is salvaging. After one day, the item is destroyed and the artificer adds the gp it took to create the item to his craft reserve. These points are lost if the artificer does not use them before gaining his next level.\n\nFor example, an artificer wants to retain the essence of a {i}wand of summon monster IV{/i} that has 20 charges. Originally created (like all wands) with 50 charges, it required 21000gp when initially made, or  420gp (21000 / 50) per charge. The artificer is able to recover the gp from the remaining charges. He puts 8400gp (420 x 20) into his craft reserve." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Salvage the gp from a magic item and use those points to create another magic item.">
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cArtMeSpTr" name="Metamagic Spell Trigger" description="At 6th level, an artificer gains the ability to apply a metamagic feat he knows to a spell trigger item (generally a wand). He must have the appropriate item creation feat for the spell trigger item he is using. Using this ability expends additional charges from the item equal to the number of effective spell levels the metamagic feat would add to a spell.{br}{br}For example, an artificer can quicken a spell cast from a wand by spending 5 charges (4 additional charges), empower the spell by spending 3 charges, or trigger it silently by spending 2 charges. The Still Spell feat confers no benefi t when applied to a spell trigger item.{br}{br}An artificer cannot use this ability when using a spell trigger item that does not have charges, such as {i}prayer beads.{/i}" compset="ClSpecial" summary="Apply metamagic feats to spell trigger items.">
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cArtMeSpCo" name="Metamagic Spell Completion" description="At 11th level, an artificer gains the ability to apply a metamagic feat he knows to a spell completion item (generally a scroll). He must have the appropriate item creation feat for the spell completion item he is using. The DC for the Use Magic Device check is equal to 20 + (3 x the modified level of the spell). For example, applying the Empower Spell feat to a scroll of {i}cone of cold,{/i} creating a 7th-level effect, has a DC of 20 + (3 x 7), or 41. An artificer can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 3 + his Int modifier." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Apply metamagic feats to spell completion items.">
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="Tracker"/>
    <tag group="Usage" tag="Day"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
~ If we're not shown, just get out now
doneif (tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] <> 1)
~if we've been replaced, get out now
doneif (tagis[Helper.SpcReplace] <> 0)

~ Uses per day is 3 + Int modifier
field[trkMax].value += 3 + #attrmod[aINT]]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cArtSkillM" name="Skill Mastery" description="At 13th level, an artificer can take 10 when making a Spellcraft or Use Magic Device check, even if stress and distractions would normally prevent him from doing so. This ability circumvents the normal rule that a character may not take 10 on a Use Magic Device check." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Take 10 on UMD and spellcraft checks even if distracted or in combat."></thing>
